OL,7,F"The claim that international law is
OL,8,Ffine as far as it goes, but can be put
OL,9,Faside when conditions change, is a
OL,10,Fclaim that was made in the early 1930s
OL,11,Fby 'realist' jurists in Germany, most
OL,12,Fnotably Carl Schmitt, whose central
OL,13,Fthesis was in essence the claim that
OL,14,Fstate power is all that counts, not
OL,15,Flaw."
